.TH "devm_gpio_request" 9 "devm_gpio_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_gpio_request \- request a GPIO for a managed device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_gpio_request
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned gpio "  ","
.BI "const char *label "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to request the GPIO for
.IP "gpio" 12
GPIO to allocate
.IP "label" 12
the name of the requested GPIO

Except for the extra \fIdev\fP argument, this function takes the
same arguments and performs the same function as
\fBgpio_request\fP.  GPIOs requested with this function will be
automatically freed on driver detach.

If an GPIO allocated with this function needs to be freed
separately, \fBdevm_gpio_free\fP must be used.
